## **What is Trend in Statistics?**

In statistics, a **trend** refers to the general direction in which data points in a dataset tend to move over time. It highlights the long-term patterns or tendencies in the data and is often used to identify underlying behaviors or insights that are not affected by short-term fluctuations. Trends are a powerful way to uncover insights in data analytics and can guide strategic decisions in various fields, including e-commerce.
